            "text": "Distant supervision , a paradigm of relation extraction ",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "where training data is created ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "by aligning facts in a database with a large unannotated corpus , ",
            "relation": "MANNER-MEANS"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "is an attractive approach for training relation extractors . <S>",
            "relation": "SAME-UNIT"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "Various models are proposed in recent literature ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "to align the facts in the database to their mentions in the corpus . <S>",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "In this paper , we discuss and critically analyse a popular alignment strategy ",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "called the \"at least one\" heuristic . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "We provide a simple , yet effective relaxation to this strategy . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "We formulate the inference procedures in training as integer linear programming ( ILP ) problems ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "and implement the relaxation to the \"at least one \" heuristic ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 11,
            "text": "via a soft constraint in this formulation . <S>",
            "relation": "MANNER-MEANS"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 14,
            "text": "Empirically , we demonstrate ",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 14,
